The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem (matroid secretary problem) and presents an algorithmic solution with a competitive ratio analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms, optimization, and combinatorics. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as it covers topics related to combinatorial optimization, matroids, and graph theory. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with a game-theoretic problem of choosing objects in a random order. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper presents an algorithmic solution to the problem. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common topic in AI. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper uses information-theoretic techniques in the analysis of the algorithm.
